cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks. The use of deep architectures such as recurrent and recursive neural networks also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on capturing structural information around an input suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of word vector representations and binary parse trees suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as well.
